ce:section.ce:para:
The XRD profile of as-obtained DPBI-based CQDs (Fig. 1
                        ) showed a broad peak centered at around 25.8° corresponds to (002) reflection planes, which is attributed to the thinness and disordered stacking of CQDs [15]. Furthermore, the HRTEM image (Fig. 2
                        ) showed that the CQDs derived from DPBI molecule have lattice fringes with interplanar distance 0.329 nm between them. Additionally, aggregation of some nanocrystals was observed due to nitrogen containing functional groups on the surface of DPBI-derived CQDs, which might have influenced in enhancing the interplanar distance [19].
